{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Ground}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Hippopotas}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Ground|prevnum=448|prev=Lucario|nextnum=450|next=Hippowdon|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Hippopotas}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Hippopotas\n|jname=ヒポポタス\n|jtranslit=Hipopotasu\n|tmname=Hippopotas\n|ndex=449\n|sdex=122\n|karea=Coastal\n|kdex=048\n|abrow=246\n|obrow=283\n|opbrow=103\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Ground\n|category=Hippo\n|height-ftin=2\'07"\n|height-m=0.8\n|weight-lbs=109.1\n|weight-kg=49.5\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Sand Stream\n|abilityd=Sand Force\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Field\n|eggcycles=30\n|evtotal=1\n|evde=1\n|expyield=66\n|oldexp=95\n|lv100exp=1,250,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Brown\n|catchrate=140\n|body=08\n|pokefordex=hippopotas\n|generation=4\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Hippopotas\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese:]] \'\'\'ヒポポタス\'\'\' \'\'Hippopotas\'\') is a {{type|Ground}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation IV]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolve]]s into {{p|Hippowdon}} starting at [[level]] 34.\n\n==Biology==\nHippopotas is a quadruped, hippo-like Pokémon that is most commonly found in deserts and other arid places. Its skin color depends on gender: if male, it is tan with dark brown patches, and if female, its coloring is reversed. It has a large snout with round, protruding nostrils. Its eyes and small ears protrude from the top of its head. Its torso has mottled coloring and a small hole on its back. Each of its feet has two blunt claws, and it has a small tail. Hippopotas spends its time bathing in sand and avoids water at all costs. It covers itself in sand as a protective measure against germs and expels sand instead of sweat. When it walks through the sand, it shuts its nostrils. It prefers to travel in groups of ten.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Hoopa Bonnie Hippopotas.png|thumb|left|220px|Hippopotas in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\n===={{DL|Recurring wild Pokémon in the anime|Hippopotas|Hippopotas (anime)}}====\nHippopotas appeared in \'\'[[DP044|Mass Hip-Po-Sis!]]\'\' and \'\'[[DP065|Sleight of Sand!]]\'\'. In both episodes, {{Ash}} and {{ashfr}} had to help him reunite with its herd of Hippowdon and fellow Hippopotas after it was accidentally separated from them.\n\n====Other====\nMultiple Hippopotas appeared in \'\'[[M18|Hoopa and the Clash of Ages]]\'\', where one of them was borrowed by Ash and his friends for its {{type|Ground}} attacks. It played a crucial role in restoring the broken [[Prison Bottle]] during the climactic battle in [[Dahara City]]. This Hippopotas was later returned to his herd, and {{an|Bonnie}} bid it farewell.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nA Hippopotas made a brief cameo appearance in \'\'[[M11|Giratina and the Sky Warrior]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn|Coordinator}}\'s Hippopotas appeared in \'\'[[DP114|Another One Gabites the Dust!]]\'\', where it was participating in the [[Contest Battle|Battle Stage]] of the {{to|Chocovine}} {{pkmn|Contest}}.\n\nA Hippopotas appeared in \'\'[[DP125|Battling a Cute Drama!]]\'\', where it was seen at the [[Shelter Town]]\'s [[Pokémon Center]].\n\nA Hippopotas appeared during a flashback in \'\'[[M19|Volcanion and the Mechanical Marvel]]\'\' as a resident of the [[Nebel Plateau]].\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP044|Hippopotas|Dawn\'s Pokédex|Hippopotas, the Hippo Pokémon. It lives in dry places and covers itself in sand to protect against germs. It does not enjoy getting wet.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Diamond & Pearl\'\'|Sinnoh}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Gentleman Hippopotas Adventures.png|thumb|130px|Hippopotas in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Darkrai Mission Story: Pokémon Ranger Vatonage - the Comic manga===\nA Hippopotas appeared in \'\'[[PRV1|A Fresh Start]]\'\'.\n\n===In the movie adaptations===\nA Hippopotas appeared in \'\'{{ma|Hoopa and the Clash of Ages}}\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nA male Hippopotas appeared in \'\'[[PS361|Bombastic Bibarel & Heroic Hippopotas]]\'\', under the ownership of a {{tc|Gentleman}} at the [[Seven Stars Restaurant]]. He appeared along with a {{tc|Madame|Socialite}} and her {{p|Bibarel}}. The quartet battled {{adv|Diamond}}\'s {{p|Torterra}}, [[Tru]], and {{adv|Pearl}}\'s {{p|Infernape}}, [[Chimler]], in a [[Multi Battle|Tag Battle]].\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Hippopotas (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===NPC appearances===\n* {{g|Super Mystery Dungeon}}: a male Hippopotas is a resident of Serene Village, and speaks with a French accent. After the player brings their partner back at the Epilogue, Hippopotas can be recruited.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Ground}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=IV}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=IV|reg1=Sinnoh|num1=122|reg2=Johto}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Diamond|entry=It lives in arid places. Instead of perspiration, it expels grainy sand from its body.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Pearl|entry=It enshrouds itself with sand to protect itself from germs. It does not enjoy getting wet.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Platinum|entry=It shuts its nostrils tight then travels through the sand as if walking. They form colonies of around ten.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=HeartGold|v2=SoulSilver|entry=It shrouds itself in sand to ward off germs. It travels easily through the sands of the desert.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=V|reg1=Unova}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black|v2=White|t=FFF|entry=It shuts its nostrils tight then travels through the sand as if walking. They form colonies of around ten.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black 2|v2=White 2|t=FFF|entry=It shuts its nostrils tight then travels through sand as if walking. They form colonies of around 10.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|num1=048|label1=Coastal|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=It lives in arid places. Instead of perspiration, it expels grainy sand from its body.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=It enshrouds itself with sand to protect itself from germs. It d